{{Refimprove|date=February 2010}} {{Infobox Software | name = nLite | logo = [[File:NLite Logo.png|64px]] | screenshot = [[File:nLite screenshot.png|300px]] | caption = nLite Wizard | developer = Dino Nuhagic (aka Nuhi) | latest_release_version = 1.4.9.1 | latest_release_date = {{Release date|2008|09|11}} | operating_system = [[Windows 2000]], [[Windows XP]] and [[Windows Server 2003]] | platform =PC | genre = [[Software remastering]] | license = [[Freeware]] <!-- "Freeware" = "Proprietary non-commercial" --> | website = [http://www.nliteos.com/ www.nliteos.com] }} {{Infobox Software | name = vLite | logo = [[File:Vlite.png|64px]] | screenshot = [[File:vLite screenshot.png|300px]] | caption = | developer = Dino Nuhagic (aka Nuhi) | latest_release_version = 1.2 Final | latest_release_date = {{Release date|2008|09|12}} | operating_system = [[Windows Vista]]<!-- The source does not mention Windows 7 or Server 2008 --> | platform =PC | genre = [[Software remastering]] | license = [[Freeware]] <!-- "Freeware" = "Proprietary non-commercial" --> | website = [http://www.vlite.net/ www.vlite.net] }} {{lowercase|nLite}} '''nLite''' and '''vLite''' are [[freeware]] [[application software|application]]s which create customized installation CDs or DVDs for [[Microsoft]] [[Windows 2000]], [[Windows XP]], [[Windows Server 2003]] and [[Windows Vista]]. nLite lets users customize and remove components from their Windows installation disc thus creating a custom version, this is most useful for system administrators or for volume installations. Nlite enables you to integrate update packages and programs otherwise included in Windows Update to simplify and speed up Windows installation. Some of the features included in Nlite are automated installation, where the process of entering a product key (volume or not), setting the administrator's password, regional settings and user account settings and names beforehand. It can also, through addons and Hotfixes, install extra third party programs automatically. nLite supports [[Windows 2000]], [[Windows XP]] (32 and 64 bit) and [[Windows Server 2003]], while vLite is made for [[Windows Vista]] (32 and 64 bit). While some people have reported success using vLite with the Windows 7 beta and the RC<ref>http://forum.eeeuser.com/viewtopic.php?id=57434 (vLite supported Windows 7 beta)</ref>. Windows 7 is not fully compatible with vLite and it is not advised to use vLite with Windows 7 due to the potential instability from is not being fully supported at the time. The creator has no intention or plans to support or release a Windows 7 compatible version<ref>{{cite web |url=http://apcmag.com/no-plans-for-7lite-reveals-vlite-creator.htm |title=No plans for â7Liteâ reveals vLite creator |publisher=[[APC Magazine]],</ref><ref>|date=29 April 2009 |accessdate=3 March 2010 |last=Ryan |first=David |quote=And although vLite does work with Windows 7 beta and the RC candidate builds, thereâs obvious interest in an updated program tailored for Windows 7.}}The company has not officially declared any release."{{Citation needed|date=October 2011}}</ref>.
